children.text: The ceiling plasterboard has not been properly fixed/screwed, with perimeter fixings to prevent the ceiling from failure.
The Victorian Building Authority’s Guide to Standards and Tolerances states in section 9.11 Plasterboard Sheeting, that
‘The installation and jointing of plasterboard sheeting systems is defective if it does not conform to AS/NZS 2589 and the manufacturer’s installation instructions’ .
The plasterboard manufacturer in their installation instructions state in the ‘Installation of Garage Ceilings section that
‘Fasten along the perimeter lines at 300mm max centres as illustrated in Figure 27’

The builder has not installed this ceiling in accordance with the manufacturer’s requirements, which puts it at risk of failure. The manufacturer should be consulted to provide a solution to this issue, and the owners should request a copy of the documentation for their records.
